{"openapi":"3.1.0","info":{"title":"Backstory Public API","version":"1.0.0","description":"The Backstory public API gives your organization programmatic read access to the go-to-market data Backstory captures and enriches: accounts, activities, contacts, leads, opportunities, teams, team members, and Engagement Levels, plus asynchronous bulk export and activity ingestion.\n\n**Base URL:** `https://api.people.ai`\n\n**Authentication:** all requests use a short-lived OAuth 2.0 bearer token. Mint one from your API key and secret (see Authentication), then send it as `Authorization: Bearer <access_token>`.\n\n**Errors:** all endpoints share one error envelope—`code`, `id`, `message`, `path`, and `timestamp` (formatted `DD-MM-YYYY HH:MM:SS`). Any endpoint may return `400` (malformed request), `401` (auth), `404` (not found), `429` (rate limit; no `Retry-After` header), or `500`.\n\n**Validation status (2026-06-03):** the GA read (GET) endpoints are validated against the live API. The mutation endpoints (`POST /pull/v1/export/activities/jobs` and `POST /pull/v1/export/contacts/jobs` job creation, and `PUT /v0/public/activities/email` ingest) and the job-data download have not been exercised live—validate them in a sandbox before relying on their request and response details.\n\n> Response schemas in this reference are derived from observed API responses and > field inventories. Field presence can vary by record and by your organization's > configuration. Replace `YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN` with a token you mint at runtime.\n"},"servers":[{"url":"https://api.people.ai","description":"Production"}],"security":[{"bearerAuth":[]}],"tags":[{"name":"Authentication","description":"Mint a bearer token from your API key and secret."},{"name":"Accounts","description":"Read account records."},{"name":"Activities","description":"Read activity records (emails, calls, meetings) and their participants."},{"name":"Contacts","description":"Read contact records."},{"name":"Leads","description":"Read lead records."},{"name":"Opportunities","description":"Read opportunity records."},{"name":"Teams","description":"Read team records."},{"name":"Team Members","description":"Read team-member (user) records."},{"name":"Engagement","description":"Read Engagement Levels for accounts, contacts, leads, and opportunities."},{"name":"Bulk Export","description":"Asynchronous, job-based export of raw activity data and enriched contacts."},{"name":"Activity Ingestion","description":"Push activities into Backstory."}],"paths":{"/auth/v1/tokens":{"post":{"tags":["Authentication"],"summary":"Generate an access token","operationId":"createAccessToken","description":"Exchange your API key (`client_id`) and secret (`client_secret`) for a short-lived bearer token using the OAuth 2.0 client-credentials grant. Generate and manage API keys in the Admin Panel under API Key Management. The returned `access_token` is a JWT; send it as `Authorization: Bearer <access_token>` on every other request. The default lifespan is 7200 seconds.\n","security":[],"requestBody":{"required":true,"content":{"application/x-www-form-urlencoded":{"schema":{"type":"object","required":["grant_type","client_id","client_secret"],"properties":{"grant_type":{"type":"string","enum":["client_credentials"],"description":"Must be `client_credentials`."},"client_id":{"type":"string","description":"Your API key from API Key Management."},"client_secret":{"type":"string","description":"Your API secret from API Key Management."}}},"example":{"grant_type":"client_credentials","client_id":"YOUR_API_KEY","client_secret":"YOUR_API_SECRET"}}}},"responses":{"200":{"description":"A bearer access token.","content":{"application/json":{"schema":{"$ref":"#/components/schemas/TokenResponse"},"example":{"access_token":"YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN","token_type":"bearer","expires_in":7200,"expires_at":"2026-06-03T07:25:25.999967"}}}},"401":{"$ref":"#/components/responses/Unauthorized"}}}},"/v0/public/accounts":{"get":{"tags":["Accounts"],"sum